channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Tim Walz condemns Hamas after being roasted for appearing to miss question about murdered hostages in Gaza
item.description: Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz appeared to miss a question about six hostages found dead in Gaza during a visit to the Minnesota State Fair on Sunday.

item.title: Democrats say Trump IVF proposal could be a lie
item.description: Former President Donald Trump's proposal for free in vitro fertilization treatments forces Democrats to play catch-up on the type of social issue they usually own and to tell voters that the Republican nominee's proposal could be too good to be true.

item.title: A Herculean Effort
item.description: This powerful story about a grieving seventh-grade boy has hope and determination at its core.

item.title: Dems Keep RFK Jr. On North Carolina Ballot As Swing State Spoiler To Hurt Trump Campaign
item.description: It’s more 'cartel' politics from the DNC, says Dennis Kucinich, the former Democrat who managed RFK Jr.’s campaign.

item.title: Biden, Harris to meet with US hostage deal negotiating team as major protests erupt in Israel
item.description: Protests in cities across Israel sparked up after the bodies of six hostages were found in an underground tunnel in Rafah, upsetting many that a cease-fire had not been struck.

item.title: Monday's Labor Day is the 143rd commemoration of holiday that started in New York
item.description: "The first Labor Day holiday was celebrated on Tuesday, September 5, 1882, in New York City, in accordance with the plans of the Central Labor Union. The Central Labor Union held its second Labor Day holiday just a year later, on September 5, 1883," advises the official history of the U.S. Labor Dept.

item.title: Why College Sports Deserve to Survive
item.description: It is an admittedly irrational system, but it inculcates student-athletes with priceless virtues on which our civilization depends.

item.title: Lawsuit: Fulton County Fails To Maintain Accurate Voter Rolls, Violating State And Federal Law
item.description: Georgia's Fulton County is allegedly not maintaining its voter rolls, according to a newly filed suit in federal court.

item.title: Israel's largest labor union plans massive strike after six hostages’ bodies recovered
item.description: The chief of Israel's largest labor union, the Histadrut Labor Federation, is planning a massive one-day strike on Monday to demand a cease-fire deal after hostages were found dead.

item.title: Gabbard warns against taking Harris lightly, notes her 'experience' on debate stage
item.description: Former Rep. Tulsi Gabbard said Vice President Kamala Harris should not be underestimated when she goes head-to-head with former President Donald Trump on the debate stage later this month.

item.title: Media Pretend That Systematic Government Censorship Is a Nothingburger
item.description: What’s the point of a press corps that’s uninterested in the freedom of the press?

item.title: Arizona Judge Upholds Block On Secretary Fontes’ Anti-Speech Election Rules
item.description: An Arizona judge upheld an injunction on Wednesday prohibiting enforcement of provisions in the state’s election guidance that her court found “restricted free speech.” Writing for the Maricopa County Superior Court of Arizona, Judge Jennifer Ryan-Touhill denied a request by Democrat Secretary of State Adrian Fontes to place a stay pending appeal on the court’s […]

item.title: Oregon reverses course and recriminalizes drug possession
item.description: Oregon, which became the first state in the country to decriminalize possession of a small amount of hard drugs, is reversing course and recriminalizing such possession.

item.title: GOP Sen. Cotton says he's 'open to' Trump IVF-coverage proposal
item.description: Sen. Tom Cotton said he is in favor of former President Donald Trump's proposal to have in vitro fertilization covered by the government or health insurance companies.

item.title: Big Government Is Leading to Smaller Families
item.description: When the government makes it harder for young adults to succeed and undermines their confidence in the future, it needs to get out of their way.

item.title: States Open The Door To Foreign-Born Presidential Candidate On Their Ballots
item.description: Shiva Ayyadurai is fighting to get on ballots, but the naturalized U.S. citizen from India fails to meet a key constitutional requirement.

item.title: Graham urges Biden, Israel to take on Iran after hostages killed, calls Harris foreign policy 'wrecking ball'
item.description: Sen. Lindsey Graham, R-S.C., condemned Iran after six Israeli hostages were found dead in Gaza, saying President Biden should target Tehran's oil refineries.

item.title: It's a pork chop on a stick and a vanilla shake for Tim Walz at the Minnesota State Fair
item.description: Democratic vice presidential nominee Tim Walz munched on a pork chop on a stick and washed it down with a vanilla shake Sunday as the Minnesota governor and his family visited his home state fair.

item.title: The American Experiment Can Endure Modern Chaos
item.description: Our country faces some of the same crises that beset ancient civilizations, but our system is better built to withstand them.

item.title: The CNN Interview Reminded People Of What Has Always Been True About Kamala
item.description: In over her head, apathetic toward governance, and lacking vision. That's the Kamala Harris CNN's interview reminded us of.
